The paper deals with the study of stratification from both geometric and topological perspectives, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of sheaf theory and partial orders with the Alexandroff topology points towards computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The study of stratification and homology also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper's focus on algorithms and their applications in topological data analysis suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
